verbs.description: [ARG0: President Donald Trump] [V: promised] [ARGM-LOC: on the campaign trail] [ARG2: to bring real life back to the American economy] , and if May 's jobs report is any indication of his work nearly 18 months into office , Trump has certainly succeeded . The report showed the American economy is growing toward a very prosperous future . And according to CNBC , that 's really great news for everyone — except Democrats . Why is it bad for Dems ? As CNBC reported , as politicians nationwide ramp up their campaign efforts ahead of November 's midterm election no issue " is more important than the perennial issue of employment . " " Voters who are employed are historically more likely to favor incumbents than those who are out of work , " CNBC reported . Indeed , May 's report showed the economy added 223,000 jobs in May , pushing the unemployment rate to just 3.8 percent , a level not seen in 18 years . In addition , the unemployment rate among African - Americans dipped to 5.9 percent , a drop …
